{
  "texts": [
    "Difficulty with literacy led to uncertainty as to the effectiveness of the person's posts, as one person with disability explained: 'I don't always know the word and know how to spell it.",
    "I don't always know if my posts are okay because of this' [21] (p. 37).",
    "Kim and Quan [27] also reported that 'most participants found it difficult to read and write content: \"Too many difficult words.",
    "It is hard\" (Participant 1) and \"Uh… When people post something there are things I do not understand\" (Participant 1), and \"If they use some difficult words, I, don't understand it so…that's a little bit hard\" (Participant 7)' (p. 417).",
    "However, poor spelling was not always a barrier and 'did not necessarily hinder text communication' [29] (p. 296)."
  ]
}